{"title":"Artfully Arranged Junkyard Objects","link":"https://kottke.org/24/10/artfully-arranged-junkyard-objects","date":1729266307000,"content":"\n        <p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/coletivos-24-01.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/coletivos-24-01.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/coletivos-24-01.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"867\" alt=\"dense photographic collage of junkyard object\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/coletivos-24-02.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/coletivos-24-02.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/coletivos-24-02.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"1300\" alt=\"dense photographic collage of junkyard object\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/coletivos-24-03.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/coletivos-24-03.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/coletivos-24-03.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"1296\" alt=\"dense photographic collage of junkyard object\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/coletivos-24-04.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/coletivos-24-04.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/coletivos-24-04.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"867\" alt=\"dense photographic collage of junkyard object\" /></p>\n\n<p>In a continuation and tweak of <a href=\"https://www.cassiovasconcellos.com/series/collectives/\">his Coletivos project</a> (which <a href=\"https://kottke.org/20/08/fantastical-overclocked-urban-scenes-by-cassio-vasconcellos\">I posted about previously</a>), C√°ssio Vasconcellos took aerial photos of scrapyards and arranged the junked cars, planes, trains, and other objects into <a href=\"https://www.cassiovasconcellos.com/series/collectives-2/\">dense photographic collages</a>.</p>\n\n<blockquote><p>OVER presents a scenario that seems to point to a dystopian future, but which, in fact, brings together fragments of the present. The exaggerated agglomeration denounces the misleading idea of ‚Äúdisposal‚Äù, given that objects do not cease to exist in the world when we throw them away. Rather, they inhabit other places.</p></blockquote>\n\n<p>This video shows the artist‚Äôs process, from hanging out the side of a helicopter to arranging all the items in Photoshop.</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n        \n\n         <p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/art\">art</a> ¬∑ <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/Cassio%20Vasconcellos\">Cassio Vasconcellos</a> ¬∑ <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/photography\">photography</a> ¬∑ <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/remix\">remix</a></p>\n\n         <p>üí¨ <a href=\"https://kottke.org/24/10/artfully-arranged-junkyard-objects\">Join the discussion on kottke.org</a> ‚Üí</p>\n\n    ","author":"Jason Kottke","siteTitle":"Kottke","siteHash":"89a883271b4598f9b33ebe87be70d38557bcd266e68aee521a8f93622e0ab723","entryHash":"8684c340e3f48ec3dcb9e45776beb4e5dcee000f6bf75c94bff7bd1477c92382","category":"Sites"}